docs.abstract: President Trump has responded to Russia’s ramped-up nuclear arsenal and cyberweapons with a mix of Cold War-era approaches and virtual silence.
docs.snippet: President Trump has responded to Russia’s ramped-up nuclear arsenal and cyberweapons with a mix of Cold War-era approaches and virtual silence.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Just hours after President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia boasted last week about producing “invincible” new nuclear arms designed to evade American missile defenses, President Trump’s nominee to command the nation’s military cyberunits was being grilled at a Senate confirmation hearing about another vexing Russian threat.

headline.main: A Russian Threat on Two Fronts Meets an American Strategic Void

docs.abstract: The president is on a charm offensive with North Korea and being heavy-handed against Iran. Both paths are risky and could prove to be dead ends.
docs.snippet: The president is on a charm offensive with North Korea and being heavy-handed against Iran. Both paths are risky and could prove to be dead ends.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After declaring he has plenty of time to solve the North Korean nuclear crisis, President Trump celebrated on Tuesday what he claimed was an early victory: satellite evidence that the country is dismantling a missile test stand in a small first step toward securing commitments made by its leader, Kim Jong-un, last month in Singapore.

docs.abstract: The companies, including Microsoft and Facebook, hope to create a Geneva Conventions for cyberspace, but none are from countries that are suspected in most of the recent attacks.
docs.snippet: The companies, including Microsoft and Facebook, hope to create a Geneva Conventions for cyberspace, but none are from countries that are suspected in most of the recent attacks.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 30 high-tech companies, led by Microsoft and Facebook, announced a set of principles on Tuesday that included a declaration that they would not help any government — including that of the United States — mount cyberattacks against “innocent civilians and enterprises from anywhere,” reflecting Silicon Valley’s effort to separate itself from government cyberwarfare.

headline.main: Tech Firms Sign ‘Digital Geneva Accord’ Not to Aid Governments in Cyberwar

docs.abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo wants to broaden negotiations to other nations, but European allies will most likely balk at his demand to forever limit Iran’s nuclear program.
docs.snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo wants to broaden negotiations to other nations, but European allies will most likely balk at his demand to forever limit Iran’s nuclear program.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will outline a new strategy on Monday for constraining Iran, centered around a demand that the United States’ European allies have already rejected: that Tehran enter negotiations in a new deal that would permanently ban Iran from any substantive manufacturing of nuclear fuel and, in turn, forever cut off a pathway to building a bomb.

headline.main: U.S. Wants to Restart Nuclear Talks With Iran, but Hasn’t Budged on Demands
headline.print_headline: U.S. Wants to Restart Nuclear Talks With Iran, but Is Firm on Demands

docs.abstract: The attorney general is a key witness in the investigation into whether Mr. Trump tried to obstruct the Russia inquiry itself.
docs.snippet: The attorney general is a key witness in the investigation into whether Mr. Trump tried to obstruct the Russia inquiry itself.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — By the time Attorney General Jeff Sessions arrived at President Trump’s Mar-a-Lago resort for dinner one Saturday evening in March 2017, he had been receiving the presidential silent treatment for two days. Mr. Sessions had flown to Florida because Mr. Trump was refusing to take his calls about a pressing decision on his travel ban.

headline.main: Trump Asked Sessions to Retain Control of Russia Inquiry After His Recusal
